'''Grand Central Publishing''' is a division of [[Hachette Book Group]]. Formerly Warner Books, Grand Central Publishing came into existence in March 2006 after Time Warner sold the Time Warner Book Group to Hachette Livre.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/06/business/worldbusiness/06iht-book.html|title=LagardÃ¨re to buy Time Warner books|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20140613/NEWS/140619920/book-publisher-hachette-brings-down-the-ax] {{dead link|date=December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediabistro.com/galleycat/warner-books-morphs-into-grand-central-publishing_b4152|title=Warner Books Morphs into Grand Central Publishing|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref>

Besides Grand Central Publishing itself, the division has four imprints: Twelve, Grand Central Life & Style, Forever, and Forever Yours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/publishers/|title=Publishing Groups - Hachette Book Group|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/publisher-news/article/50250-grand-central-to-launch-digital-romance-imprint.html|title=Grand Central to Launch Digital Romance Imprint|work=PublishersWeekly.com|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.geminis.ufscar.br/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/shouldyouinvestinthelongtail.pdfx] {{dead link|date=December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtbookreviews.com/rt-daily-blog/breaking-news-grand-central-publishing-expanding-its-romance-imprints|title=Breaking News: Grand Central Publishing Is Expanding Its Romance Imprints|publisher=|accessdate=13 December 2014}}</ref>

